{
  "text": "Note that for k \u2208 1/2 + Z the space M k,\u03c1 of holomorphic modular forms of weight k for \u03c1 is isomorphic to the space J * k+1/2,N of skew-holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight k + 1/2 and index N , and M k,\u03c1 is isomorphic to the space J k+1/2,N of holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight k + 1/2 and index N (see [CITATION_1] , Section 5). In particular, one can view \u03b8 1/2 and \u03b8 3/2 as skew-holomorphic Jacobi forms of weight 1 and 2. Further, we will make frequent use of a result by Skoruppa which asserts that M 1/2,\u03c1 \u223c = J 1,N = {0} for all N (see [CITATION_2] , Theorem 5.7).",
